column1: This #Thanksgiving may look a little different because of #COVID19 but there is still so much to be grateful for despite this year's hardships. I'm grateful for the resiliency that Americans show time and time again.  Be safe and have a happy Thanksgiving! https://t.co/z7FbYvb8aw

This pandemic is continuing to take an economic toll and we need to ensure families and small businesses are still supported.  @GovInslee announced additional support for families and businesses impacted by the #COVID19 pandemic - you can learn more here: https://t.co/pBltZHTo6w

A new #COVID19 testing site opened Friday at Highline College in south King County. The testing site is free for everyone regardless of if you have health insurance.  As cases continue to rise I urge you to be safe get tested and help slow the spread. https://t.co/8kBxc0jxhJ

Today I voted to advance the National Apprenticeship Act which would create 1 million new apprenticeship opportunities to help Americans get back to work. This is critical to building back our workforce in the face of the economic downturn due to the #COVID19 pandemic. https://t.co/AQced7cdKH
